name: Rain Incubator - COVID Vaccine Clinic
vaccines: Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine, Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine
info:
Tacoma Community College (TCC) is partnering with RAIN (a non-profit providing biotech start-up facilities and student training in STEM fields) to bring TCC students, faculty, staff, and our surrounding community more opportunities to access vaccinations. No one over the age of 16 will be refused vaccination if they pass the screening questions during sign-up (anyone is eligible).

Tuesday, August 10th we will hold vaccine clinics on the Tacoma Campus from 11 am-2 pm and 4 pm-6 pm in Building 9. Participants can park with no pass in Parking Lot E, off of Mildred Street, and take the ramp or stairs up to Building 9. You will check-in outside Building 9 at the canopy. Please call campus safety if you need assistance at (253) 566-5111.

Both Pfizer and Moderna vaccines will be available.

It is VERY important that you show up for your appointment as not doing so risks precious vaccines being wasted. Please come to Building 9 at your appointment time-DO NOT wait for a text. Walk-ins are available but may require a wait time. If you are waitlisted and are able to get an appointment through a cancellation on PrepMod.com. All patients who do not check-in within 20 minutes of their scheduled time risk appointment cancellation. We will send out an email to schedule the second dose at a future time. Please come get vaccinated and support your community and fellow Titans by slowing the spread! 

FULL meals will be provided to all who register!
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
